(I'm very very late but)
Dear Soulmate,
If you are who I think you might be,  just give me time. I'm sorry I can't be the person you deserve. You are beautiful and wonderful and I have so much hope for your (our?) future. I think about you every day and thinking about your smile makes me smile so much. Thank you for the laughter and the joy you give me. Thank you for waiting. Thank you for understanding that I'm not ready for you yet. I truly, honestly believe that if we're meant to be it will happen. Whether that's five months or five years from now, it will happen. Thank you for everything you've given me and thank you for listening. Thank you for texting me randomly and staying up late with me and being the amazing person you are. Thank you for understanding as I questioned my sexuality and always being my rock. Thank you for never letting me down. Thank you for never making me feel like less than I am. You make me want to be better. Because of you I am better. I think I'm falling in love with you, just a little every day, and I can't wait to tell you someday. I'll hold you in my heart forever, sunshine. No matter what, no matter how many miles are between us, I am here for you. I promise. Thank you, thank you, thank you. Maybe one day I'll tell you all this. For now, just know I'm sending you smiles from thousands of miles away. 

Love (someday),
Your sunshine

Comment: Thereâ€™s a girl. Iâ€™ve known her since the 4th grade. I was new in school and wasnâ€™t happy at the time. A friend of her introduced me to her and her friend group which was pretty big and all were friendly. Even then, I didnâ€™t talk to her as much compared to the other people. But I wasnâ€™t as connected to those people either, but they were friends. She was odd and different from the rest. I would think she was too different for me to be friends with. Her mother invited us over a lot and had sleepovers because her house was the only one big enough. Even then, she was just another friend. We grew up together so the friendship becomes natural. It wasnâ€™t until middle school around 7th grade. For some reason, she started to stand out from the social group. I was drawn to her. I started to look forward to seeing her in school and whenever there was sleepovers, I was the first one there. I started to trust her and she opened up and it was beautiful. To this day I have no idea what was it that made it tick in my head or what caused that change but goddamn was it a hit in the face. We continue to grow up together. 8th grade comes around and we are the closest of friends and everyone can see it. She changed but I adored her anyways. She was more confident and herself and I adored everything of her. She started to branch out to other friend groups and I was shy but followed her around anyways. As long as I was there I was happy. Neither of us understood why. One day she noticed and said, â€œyou donâ€™t have to follow me always, you know,â€. That moment, I panicked. I havenâ€™t even realized I followed her that often. Why? Why did I do that? Why am I panicked about it? It was that night where I realized I had grown fond of her. I couldnâ€™t have. We were 8th graders. Girls donâ€™t love other girls. Not that way. I strayed far from her afterwards. When I was ready, I came out. She was the first I came out to. I trusted her with my life. And I confessed to. My chest bursted when she said she doesnâ€™t feel that way. I understood, we were still the closest of friends. That summer, I got a boyfriend out of pressure. I am bisexual but he didnâ€™t make me feel happy like I did when I texted her. I broke up with him. She came out to me that year but was closested. I supported her. We supported each other. We got into different high schools. We texted everyday. Even if wasnâ€™t a conversation, we probably just sent memes every other day just to let each other know we are still there. I was surprised when our mutual friends said they lost touch with her. How could you lose touch with such an amazing person? No matter how many friends Iâ€™ve lost, she was always there. Highschool was weird for us. I think itâ€™s because the stress came in and the sleepover stopped. Sophomore year comes around and she tells me to come over to her house, something I havenâ€™t been able to do since highschool. She confessed to me and asked me to be her girlfriend. Sheâ€™s still closested but goddamn me if I was to pass up this opportunity. I had thought I had lost those feelings until she whispered if she could kiss me. I froze instantly when it happened and sometimes I feel her lips linger on mine if I close my eyes and remember. My first kiss and I made a fool of myself when I literally couldnâ€™t move by how overwhelmed I was. Time goes by. Pet names come, more romantic cheesy memes sent. Little dates that took ages to plan but weâ€™re worth it just to have her head leaned on my shoulder in the movies and have her hold my hand even if it was a moment. No one knew of what we were. My favorite thing about her is when she texts me in 1 in the morning cheesy things because she knows Iâ€™m asleep by 12 and would like to not feel embarrassed by an equally cheesy response. Sometimes I surprise her with being awake and doing it first. But above all, we still were the closest of friends. We were open with our problems and victories. She was too good to be true. But of course it wasnâ€™t perfect. I had to ask her to junior prom with a secret note and she said yes. I havenâ€™t danced with her since the 8th grade dance where girls dancing with each other was normal. I dreamed of the day of seeing her with her gown and being able to hold her close. I wore blue, her favorite color. She never came. I cried all night. She never responded back to my messages. Until a week later. It was a personal conversation so Iâ€™ll spare the details but I forgave her because I understood and adored her still. I was just happy she didnâ€™t abandon me completely. We continued our secret. We spent more time together. I could listen to her rant about anything and Iâ€™d listen as much I could but I was always in a trance when with her. The moment I realized sheâ€™s my soulmate? Or at least sheâ€™s the closest thing i could get of a soulmate? When she held me close in her living room while ranting and talking about every detail they messed up on Mamma Mia 1 and 2 while making me watch it after finding out I never had before. She apologized for distracting me from the movie but she was so passionate about it she couldnâ€™t stop talking . Even so, I was distracted anyways. She is the person who understood all of me and I understood her as much as she tried to show me. I love her. Sometimes I mention mamma Mia just to have her rant about it again and make me remember that night. We were young. We are still young. Senior year highschool comes in. In my spring break, I buy her flowers and a cheesy sign for a promprosal. I go to her house by surprise. Surprise for me because her mom answered the door. I hid the poster and made an excuse of the flowers. Her mom was with us and my idea of a romantic promposal changed with a simple question if she wanted to go this time. She said sheâ€™ll think about it. Is it always going to be this way? Will I ever see the day where I donâ€™t have to lock a door to kiss her? The next day, I get a text saying Iâ€™m not going to like what sheâ€™ll say, I think â€œok, no prom date again, hahaâ€ she says, â€œWe canâ€™t do this anymoreâ€ again, personal conversation and details spared, she tells me that weâ€™re getting older and she doesnâ€™t know what would be our future. She thought of last year prom, she would hate to do it not only again, but for the rest of our lives, she accepts knowing she may never marry, but knows that I, a hopeless romantic, should be with someone who can fully appreciate and be present with me. I tell her that she is all that I need and want and that we can make it work. She says she knows that deep down, Iâ€™m lying. She says I donâ€™t have to be selfless anymore. I really was known to give me all to someone. She really did wear me out in all honesty. I cried for a week. We ended things in a good term but we didnâ€™t talk for a month until I was ready to go back to the things were before our sophomore year. And it was better than I expected. Like nothing changed, we are still the closest of friends and maybe even closer now. I know that we have each other backs no matter what. We are still young. Life changes and goes on. I still miss the love we had and she knows it. Sometimes, we accidentally call each other sweetheart and dear like we did. We never point it out. She does it more often than I do. It hurts when I do it but when she does it, Iâ€™m confused but still feel a longing. I havenâ€™t loved a person since. I tried. But genuinely, I believe she is my soulmate, romantic or not. And Iâ€™m scared of losing her. So even if it means being confused by the pet names and still be her friend, Iâ€™ll take it. Time changes, she is becoming more confident in herself and who she is and have told me about thinking of coming out. Weâ€™re planning to meet up again. Havenâ€™t seen her in person since the failed promposal. I hate having hope of the little sparks that are still there. Is it being selfish to be so selfless? It feels like it. But time changes and who knows, maybe one day, weâ€™ll be together again or maybe not, either way, as long as I donâ€™t lose her, I believe I can be fine. Weâ€™ll see.
